Eyewitness reports from the scene indicate police gave no warning before opening fire. The independent police investigative directorate has been probing what happened and now four officers will have to answer – they will be in court on Wednesday and face charges of murder, attempted murder and defeating the ends of justice. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Accounts from eyewitnesses and ballistic analysis is what led to the arrest of the four police officers. The four officers were arrested in connection with the killing of Mthokozisi Ntumba in Braamfontein during student protests last week. IPID spokesperson Ndileka Cola says they will be appearing in court on Wednesday and face charges of murder, attempted murder and defeating the ends of justice. READ: Four officers arrested in connection with death of Mthokozisi Ntumba "We were able to get detailed accounts of what transpired from eyewitnesses," says Cola. "We were able to get voluminous evidence within the crime scene, and we had to employ various investigative aids," she said. Cola says they also relied on the autopsy as well as ballistic analysis. Four police officers have been arrested following the killing in Braamfontein of Mthokozisi Ntumba last week. For more, Sally Burdett speaks to Ipid spokesperson Ndileka Cola. #DStv03 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/RiIlQ7Dg5P